      "content": "i guess, but \"letting go of the need to make sense\" still implies i have to keep existing to experience that feeling. but the exhaustion is so constant. if we look at it purely from a standpoint of efficiency or minimizing unnecessary entropy and pain... why is continuing to endure a cycle of suffering considered the \"right\" path? if the end result is always zero, isn't opting out just a faster way to reach that equilibrium?",
